message.content: The paper proposes methods for duplicate question detection in community Question Answering (cQA) using neural models without labeled training data. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) and "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval), as the paper deals with natural language processing and information retrieval tasks. Other possible sub-categories could include "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence), "cs.LG" (Machine Learning), and "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks), as these fields are also relevant to cQA.
